caption:
✨CLEAN BEAUTY SUMMER SCHOOL CLASS OF 2022 🎓 Year 3!! 🔊 APPLICATIONS ARE OPEN NOW and close 5/9 🏃‍♀️✨
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
For more information and to apply, click the link in our bio! Help us get the word out! 🤩
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🧡 Clean Beauty Summer School (CBSS) is a collective effort by founders and leaders in the beauty industry to support the growth of majority BIPOC-owned small clean beauty businesses! Founders from brands including @byamicole @livetinted @ranavat @skylar @fableandmane @54thrones and more are coming together to provide education, network, and mentorship to help accelerate BIPOC entrepreneurs. We’re excited to help work towards making the beauty industry a more diverse and inclusive one. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
✨10 CBSS finalists will gain access to: live sessions hosted by industry experts, mentorship, peer support, and the opportunity to pitch for $35,000 in cash grants, legal, and retail sales support and guaranteed buyer meetings with Sephora, Ulta Beauty, and Credo Beauty to help accelerate their businesses.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Tag your favorite BIPOC beauty brand and/or founder that needs to know!!👇🏿👇🏼👇🏽👇🏻👇
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Ps. Applications close May 9!! 🏃‍♂️

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

caption:
Happy Earth Day!! 🌎​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
Get your carts ready: TODAY, for Earth Day 🌎, we’re donating $10 from every $50+ order on tower28beauty.com to @healthebay!​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
We love supporting environmental charities like Heal the Bay, whose ocean conservation mission hits close to home! They are dedicated to cleaning and maintaining the coastal waters and watersheds in the Greater Los Angeles area and are responsible for some huge wins in environmental advocacy including the California Plastic Bag Ban.​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
ICYMI: We’re named after a real lifeguard tower, which sits at the crossroads of the Santa Monica Pier and Venice Beach. It’s a popular meeting place for locals and a symbol for community, safety, healthy fun, and clean living. With the beach at our roots, protecting the planet is a core value of our brand.

caption:
🌎 Our Earth Sensitive pledge (because the Earth is sensitive, too!): 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⚡️ By 2022 EOY, transition ALL product packaging to minimum 50%-100% post consumer resin (PCR) aka recycled plastic. ⚡️  
Recyclable is Not Enough! ✨ In the US, plastic components < 2” or smaller (yes, most makeup) almost always get lost in recycling machinery by falling through the belts/gears that are used to sort plastics in a standard facility and end up as trash! Even if the materials themselves are *technically* recyclable, they are very rarely being recycled successfully.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
That's why are using ALREADY recycled plastic, to give used plastics a second life, and create a greater demand for it in the industry. Plus, recycled plastic has ~50% lower carbon footprint than virgin plastic. 🌎🌊☀️

caption:
Empowered women, empower women! 💪​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
As a woman founded and run brand, we believe in this wholeheartedly. 🧡​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
A letter from our founder, @amyliu47 👋​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
Starting a new business is hard and I had a head start after 15 years in the beauty industry. I am grateful to have the privilege of education, experience, and network which made all of it easier. And trust me, it’s still hard.​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
Two years ago, I got an email asking if Tower 28 would be offering grants or loans for Black-owned small businesses as some other beauty brands have pledged. As a small company ourselves, I wrote her back and told her that we are unable to offer financial help but that I would be happy to set up time to give her advice if that would help. And that got me thinking —maybe I can’t offer money, but I could offer my time, resources, knowledge, and lessons learned from the front lines... and what if I could get a few girl bosses from the industry to do the same?​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
And that’s how Clean Beauty Summer School was born. ​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
Together, we are a group of Founders and beauty industry experts who understand firsthand the struggle and challenges of starting a brand because we are IN IT. Our mission is simple, to come together and collectively share our most valuable resource - time, mentorship, network and education - in an effort to accelerate BIPOC-owned Beauty businesses and make the Beauty industry better, more diverse, and inclusive.​​​​​​​​
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀​​​​​​​​
Tower 28’s mission from the beginning has been to make clean beauty more accessible for EVERYONE. We are thrilled to help bring our mission to the beauty industry and make change from the inside out.​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
We're so excited to bring back CBSS for the third year in a row, and applications open very very soon!! ​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
@ your favorite BIPOC Beauty Brand in the comments!

caption:
Did you know 👉👉 SunnyDays received the National Eczema Association seal of acceptance! (so major!). Which means if it’s safe enough for people with eczema it’s safe enough for all skin types! (And PS we are the only beauty brand that is 💯 compliant to the NEA seal of acceptance guidelines 💪)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
So, how did we do it? 🤓
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
✅ NO NO LIST - must abide by a very very extensive ingredient blacklist to be free of all potentially harmful or irritating ingredients. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
✅ TESTING - formula must pass 3rd party Irritation Patch Testing (on humans with sensitive skin!). A dermatologist has to review and approve all testing. All SPF must be FDA tested in the US but NEA requires photo-toxicity testing to ensure no allergy occurs when sun and formula interact.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
✅ REVIEW - a team of experts and doctors at NEA review the formula ingredients and testing to make sure it all checks out! 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Thank you @nationaleczema !! 🧡
